faculty that the teaching

00:46:59.970 --> 00:47:03.570
methods they're using are
not the best ones out there

00:47:03.570 --> 00:47:04.419
or that the thing--

00:47:04.419 --> 00:47:06.960
the specific thing that you're
proposing that's going to take

00:47:06.960 --> 00:47:09.600
a long time for them to learn
and implement successfully

00:47:09.600 --> 00:47:12.330
and may be a failure-- it
may not be the right thing--

00:47:12.330 --> 00:47:14.640
to persuade them that
that's worth trying

00:47:14.640 --> 00:47:16.740
and that it's better,
that specific thing

00:47:16.740 --> 00:47:18.780
is better than the specific
thing they're doing.

00:47:18.780 --> 00:47:20.370
Because I can recognize
that what I'm doing

00:47:20.370 --> 00:47:21.690
might not be 100%
the best thing.

00:47:21.690 --> 00:47:23.523
But how do I know that
what you're proposing

00:47:23.523 --> 00:47:24.600
is even better?

00:47:24.600 --> 00:47:26.850
So am I going to read
all the literature?

00:47:26.850 --> 00:47:30.150
And so it's partly
sustaining the interest,

00:47:30.150 --> 00:47:32.530
but it's partly just
the initial inertia.

00:47:32.530 --> 00:47:35.400
So I assume that what
you're doing already

00:47:35.400 --> 00:47:38.760
is getting people who
have taken the plunge

00:47:38.760 --> 00:47:42.722
and sending them on the
road to say, I loved this,

00:47:42.722 --> 00:47:44.430
and here's how my
classroom works better.

00:47:44.430 --> 00:47:46.304
And I think Harvard
Magazine and other places

00:47:46.304 --> 00:47:48.590
have done a great
job of spotlighting--

00:47:48.590 --> 00:47:51.910
shining a spotlight on
specific teaching innovations,

00:47:51.910 --> 00:47:55.410
including flipped classrooms
and having boosters.

00:47:55.410 --> 00:47:58.740
And then, you get a little
bored teaching the same thing

00:47:58.740 --> 00:48:00.270
the same way over time.

00:48:00.270 --> 00:48:04.584
And so having these
opportunities to be led down

00:48:04.584 --> 00:48:06.000
a different path
and not just have

00:48:06.000 --> 00:48:08.670
to walk down it
on your own is, I

00:48:08.670 --> 00:48:13.910
think, the great thing
about being here.

00:48:13.910 --> 00:48:15.920
I am keenly aware that
we are the only thing

00:48:15.920 --> 00:48:19.040
standing between you and lunch,
and that is a terrible position

00:48:19.040 --> 00:48:19.760
in which to be.

00:48:19.760 --> 00:48:21.260
I'll enjoy the power
for one second.

00:48:21.260 --> 00:48:23.180
All right, now, I think
it's time for lunch.

00:48:23.180 --> 00:48:25.130
Let me just thank
my fellow panelists.

00:48:25.130 --> 00:48:28.490
